senses.sense_definition: A surname of Spanish or Italian origin.

examples.text: Mr. <w>Rosario</w> has worked at the company for twenty years.
She decided to keep her maiden name, <w>Rosario</w>, after she got married.

senses.sense_definition: A major city and port in the province of Santa Fe, Argentina.

examples.text: The famous football player was born in <w>Rosario</w>, Argentina.
Ships transport grain down the river from the port of <w>Rosario</w>.

senses.sense_definition: The name of several municipalities in the Philippines, located in provinces such as Cavite, Batangas, and La Union.

examples.text: We took a long bus ride to visit family in <w>Rosario</w>.
The festival in <w>Rosario</w> attracts many tourists from nearby towns.
